<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER - REMOVE AND INSTALL - FUEL,
        VOLTS, WATER OR ENGINE OIL GAUGES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s08298004" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FUEL, VOLTS, WATER OR ENGINE OIL GAUGES</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08298_116.xml" xrefid="f08298551">EGC Exploded View</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>The Fuel, Volts, Water and Engine Oil Gauges may be integral components of the EGC circuit board. If
                they are not separate gauges they can be removed and replaced by scoring the perforated line between the
                gauges and the main circuit board and snapping the circuit board. The replacement gauge is fastened to
                the EGC body with two screws and connected to the main circuit board with the supplied cable with
                connectors.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08298552" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298552.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Typical EGC Circuit Board Gauge Connector Location</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>(1106) ECONOMY SWITCH CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>(1500) INSTRUMENT PANEL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>(1555) WARNING LIGHTS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The speedometer and tachometer cannot be individually replaced. If the speedometer or tachometer fail,
                the entire circuit board must be replaced.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
